You have to install the following libraries in order to build:
* wxWidget 2.8
* botan 1.10
* boost

You also need a compiler which supports C++11

In Unix, you can build with the following commands:
	cmake .
	make
The files will be written to ./build/

In Windows, you can install Code::Blocks and run The Uncrackable Encryption Toolchain [WINDOWS].cbp
Then, configurate the path of the libraries in build option.
Then press "Compile"
The executables will be written to .\win32\bin\
